My rough knowledge about Mr Tesla was him being a sort competent inventor who got outmanevoured by everyone else, so this probably fits

So, we can actually figure out what Tesla liked! We know he loved art and music and enjoyed talking about it with his friends. He lived in NYC in 1886, having moved to the US from Paris. The chance he went to a NY Philharmonic concert given his background was probably high. They played Dvorak's brand new Symphony #7 on January 9th 1886. Nicola Tesla probably would want to hear something new, as that makes for better conversation.

Given what we know about Tesla, I think this is a good guess.
